  <main class="container">
    <section id="features" class="card">
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Monitors soil moisture, temperature and humidity in real-time</li>
        <li>Automatic pump control with configurable thresholds or ML-based decisions</li>
        <li>Works for farms, home gardens, office plants and flower beds</li>
        <li>Offline-capable demo dashboard for presentations</li>
        <li>Includes synthetic dataset for model prototyping</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="how" class="card">
      <h2>How BloomIQ works</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Sensors (soil moisture probe, DHT11/22 for temp/humidity, optional light sensor) collect environmental data.</li>
        <li>An ESP32 reads sensors and applies watering logic (rule-based or ML model).</li>
        <li>A relay switches a water pump or solenoid valve to irrigate when needed.</li>
        <li>Optional GSM module can send SMS alerts; data can be logged locally or sent to a cloud/dashboard.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

